name: Peas (somerwood)
shortDescription: A heavy cropping pea with excellent taste and texture.
fullDescription: A heavy cropping pea with excellent taste and texture. Dark green in colour with standard leaf and medium sieve size. Excellent source of vitamins A, C and folate. These Pea's are excellent in flavour and disease resistant especially to powdery Mildew. Pod shape: Straight / pointed Vine length: 65-75cm Pod. Length: 100mm

name: Potatoes
fullDescription: The versatile and comforting staple loved by people all around the world. Embrace the culinary possibilities and experience the warm, comforting embrace of potatoes in your favorite dishes.

name: Pineapples
shortDescription: Tropical delight with a tangy twist.
fullDescription: Pineapples are a tropical treasure bursting with flavor. They are not only delicious but also packed with essential nutrients. These spiky wonders are a fantastic source of vitamin C, which is essential for a healthy immune system. They also contain bromelain, an enzyme that may aid digestion and reduce inflammation.

name: Bananas (Cavendish)
fullDescription: BOTANICAL NAME: Musa Acuminata Cavendish bananas are the most common variety. They are the long yellow, slightly sweet bananas. They are an excellent source of vitamin B and a good source of potassium, fiber, magnesium, and phosphorus

name: Groundnuts
shortDescription: Discover the delightful crunch and rich
fullDescription: Discover the delightful crunch and rich, earthy flavor of our Golden Crunch groundnuts. These golden-hued treasures are a nutritional powerhouse, packed with protein, healthy fats, and essential nutrients. Whether enjoyed as a satisfying snack or added to your favorite recipes, our groundnuts bring a burst of energy to your day. With their disease-resistant nature and vibrant foliage, these groundnuts are a testament to nature's resilience and goodness.

name: Macadamia nuts
shortDescription: Tree nuts that have a subtle, butter-like flavor and creamy texture.
fullDescription: Tree nuts that have a subtle, butter-like flavor and creamy texture. They are a significant source of iron, calcium, vitamin B, and phosphorus, as well as monounsaturated fats, including palmitoleic acid, a rare monounsaturated fatty acid that can aid in fat metabolism, possibly reducing the fat stored in the body. Macadamia nuts also contain moderate amounts of vitamin A, riboflavin, niacin, and flavonoids.

name: Broccoli (Batavia)
shortDescription: Vigorous early broccoli with nutty sweet flavor.
fullDescription: Vigorous early broccoli with nutty sweet flavor. Large central heads are followed by multiple side shoots for extended harvests. The curd contains the most fiber, while broccoli leaves are highest in cell-protecting antioxidants, vitamins E and K, and calcium. Strong disease resistance. Shape: dome curd shape Size: 500g - 600g curd weight Firm curd
